    {
      "index": 0,
      "paperIndex": 0,
      "speaker": "A",
      "text": "So this paper claims transformers can be made dramatically faster. Is that actually true?",
      "startMs": 0,
      "endMs": 5884,
      "figure": null,
      "image": null,
      "attribution": null
    },
    {
      "index": 1,
      "paperIndex": 0,
      "speaker": "B",
      "text": "Mostly, yes. The trick is to attend to a learned subset of tokens instead of all of them.",
      "startMs": 6234,
      "endMs": 13657,
      "figure": 1,
      "image": "images/p00-figure-1.png",
      "attribution": "Figure 1 — Rivera et al., 2024 (arXiv:2401.01234)"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "paperIndex": 0,
      "speaker": "A",
      "text": "So instead of every word looking at every other word, the model picks a few important ones?",
      "startMs": 14007,
      "endMs": 21045,
      "figure": 1,
      "image": "images/p00-figure-1.png",
      "attribution": "Figure 1 — Rivera et al., 2024 (arXiv:2401.01234)"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "paperIndex": 0,
      "speaker": "B",
      "text": "Exactly. Figure two shows the sparsity pattern the model discovers on its own.",
      "startMs": 21395,
      "endMs": 26895,
      "figure": 2,
      "image": "images/p00-figure-2.png",
      "attribution": "Figure 2 — Rivera et al., 2024 (arXiv:2401.01234)"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "paperIndex": 0,
      "speaker": "A",
      "text": "And that grid is what saves all the computation? Great tradeoff.",
      "startMs": 27245,
      "endMs": 31975,
      "figure": 2,
      "image": "images/p00-figure-2.png",
      "attribution": "Figure 2 — Rivera et al., 2024 (arXiv:2401.01234)"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "paperIndex": 1,
      "speaker": "A",
      "text": "Why do language models get worse on really long documents?",
      "startMs": 32875,
      "endMs": 37221,
      "figure": null,
      "image": null,
      "attribution": null
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "paperIndex": 1,
      "speaker": "B",
      "text": "They lose track of the middle. Figure one shows accuracy falling as the document grows.",
      "startMs": 37571,
      "endMs": 43840,
      "figure": 1,
      "image": "images/p01-figure-1.png",
      "attribution": "Figure 1 — Chen et al., 2024 (arXiv:2402.05678)"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "paperIndex": 1,
      "speaker": "A",
      "text": "So how does retrieval fix that?",
      "startMs": 44190,
      "endMs": 46997,
      "figure": 1,
      "image": "images/p01-figure-1.png",
      "attribution": "Figure 1 — Chen et al., 2024 (arXiv:2402.05678)"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "paperIndex": 1,
      "speaker": "B",
      "text": "A small retriever picks the most relevant passages first, as figure two illustrates.",
      "startMs": 47347,
      "endMs": 52847,
      "figure": 2,
      "image": "images/p01-figure-2.png",
      "attribution": "Figure 2 — Chen et al., 2024 (arXiv:2402.05678)"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "paperIndex": 1,
      "speaker": "A",
      "text": "And only those go into the model, so the answers stay grounded.",
